  {
    "object": "block",
    "id": "133c2e3e-d749-4eab-b033-cd42b1c3c59a",
    "parent": {
      "type": "page_id",
      "page_id": "bea22886-2a87-49a5-b3f2-50a5e4e52cdc"
    },
    "created_time": "2022-07-12T05:27:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2022-07-12T06:23:00.000Z",
    "created_by": {
      "object": "user",
      "id": "a89840a5-a507-41f8-ad65-4d62341efbc9"
    },
    "last_edited_by": {
      "object": "user",
      "id": "a89840a5-a507-41f8-ad65-4d62341efbc9"
    },
    "has_children": false,
    "in_trash": false,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "paragraph": {
      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "6am alarm. I’m already awake, Jordan is too. Grabbing phones, tapping away to stop the noise. Two things are confirmed - the Uber is on time, and Jordan’s COVID result is negative. Celebration and relief. \n\nSaying goodbye to Jordan is always so hard. I really love spending time with her, and this morning she was especially soft and warm. This would mark the first time this year that I was the one flying away from her; which are easier shoes to be wearing. \n\nGoodbye to you Jordan. This visit has been so beautiful. In four days I feel that I was both able to dip a toe into your Joburg life of independence as well as spend some one on one time with you that really makes me feel supported, loved, inspired and comforted. I have a feeling that I will see you again sooner than expected. \n\nThe Uber ride is made significant by the fact that the driver has a second phone up on the dashboard. It’s playing Youtube videos of American political talk shows. I observe emotions of deep frustration and irritation for the presenters. I let those feelings go and really listened to what they had to say; a sort of pro-trump propaganda, deeply emotive examples being used against Biden and honestly a huge lack of compassion. It’s quite sad to see.",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "6am alarm. I’m already awake, Jordan is too. Grabbing phones, tapping away to stop the noise. Two things are confirmed - the Uber is on time, and Jordan’s COVID result is negative. Celebration and relief. \n\nSaying goodbye to Jordan is always so hard. I really love spending time with her, and this morning she was especially soft and warm. This would mark the first time this year that I was the one flying away from her; which are easier shoes to be wearing. \n\nGoodbye to you Jordan. This visit has been so beautiful. In four days I feel that I was both able to dip a toe into your Joburg life of independence as well as spend some one on one time with you that really makes me feel supported, loved, inspired and comforted. I have a feeling that I will see you again sooner than expected. \n\nThe Uber ride is made significant by the fact that the driver has a second phone up on the dashboard. It’s playing Youtube videos of American political talk shows. I observe emotions of deep frustration and irritation for the presenters. I let those feelings go and really listened to what they had to say; a sort of pro-trump propaganda, deeply emotive examples being used against Biden and honestly a huge lack of compassion. It’s quite sad to see.",
          "href": null
        }
      ],
      "color": "default"
    },
    "archived": false
  },
